cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the modelling and analysis of software systems and their interfaces.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the analysis and maintenance of global properties in System of Systems engineering.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper proposes the use of Object Constraint Language (OCL) to enrich the Contract pattern.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with the integration of new constituent elements in a System of Systems.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses a case study in audio/video content streaming.
